properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 27 at 2:30AM MST until January 27 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...AREAS OF SNOW AND BLOWING SNOW TO IMPACT MONDAY COMMUTES ACROSS
CARBON COUNTY...

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 6 to 11
inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Snowy and Sierra Madre Ranges including Centennial and
Albany.

* WHEN...Now through 11 PM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to impossible. Patchy
blowing snow could significantly reduce visibility. Folks in the
back country should exercise caution and pack accordingly in
case of becoming disoriented due to blowing snow and low
visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM MST THIS EVENING
